/></span></strong></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.88); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, "Noto Sans", sans-serif, "Apple Color Emoji", "Segoe UI Emoji", "Segoe UI Symbol", "Noto Color Emoji"; font-size: 14px;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="box-sizing: border-box; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><br /></span></strong></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>The phrase "think for yourself" is a foundational concept in Western thought, most famously defined by Immanuel Kant during the Enlightenment.</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>1. Immanuel Kant (The Enlightenment)</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>Kant provided the definitive philosophical framework for this idea in his 1784 essay, An Answer to the Question: What Is Enlightenment?.Â </b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>"Enlightenment is manâ€™s emergence from his self-incurred tutelage."</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>Self-Incurred Tutelage (or Immaturity): Kant describes this as the inability to use one's own understanding without direction from another. It is "self-incurred" not because of a lack of intelligence, but due to a lack of courage and resolution to think independently.</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>Sapere Aude!: This Latin phrase, meaning "Dare to know!" or "Have the courage to use your own reason," was declared by Kant as the motto of the Enlightenment.Â </b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>2. Voltaire (Enlightenment/Tolerance)</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>A contemporary of the Enlightenment era, Voltaire championed intellectual freedom and pluralism.</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>"Think for yourself and let others enjoy the privilege of doing so too."</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>"Dare to think for yourself."Â </b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>3. Socrates (Classical Philosophy)</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>The phrase is often attributed to Socrates as a summary of his method of questioning (the Socratic Method).</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>"To find yourself, think for yourself."</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>Note: While this exact wording is common in modern citations, the sentiment is derived from his dialogues regarding self-knowledge and the "unexamined life".Â </b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>4. Henry David Thoreau (Transcendentalism)</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>Thoreau focused on individual autonomy against societal pressures in 19th-century America.</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>"Think for yourself, or others will think for you without thinking of you."Â </b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>5. Modern and Pop Culture Attributions</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>Coco Chanel: "The most courageous act is still to think for yourself. Aloud."</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>Timothy Leary: "Think for yourself and question authority." This became a defining slogan of the 1960s counterculture.</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>The Beatles: "Think for Yourself" is a song by George Harrison (1965), which warns against being led astray by others' lies: "I've got a word or two to say about the things that you do / You're telling all those lies about the good that we can have / If we close our eyes".</b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><b><span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"></span></b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;"><span face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" style="color: red;"><span style="font-size: 14px; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><b>Christopher Hitchens: "Take the risk of thinking for yourself. Much more happiness, truth, beauty, and wisdom will come to you that way."Â </b></span></span></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.88); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, "Noto Sans", sans-serif, "Apple Color Emoji", "Segoe UI Emoji", "Segoe UI Symbol", "Noto Color Emoji"; font-size: 14px;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="box-sizing: border-box; white-space-collapse: preserve;"><br /></span></strong></p><p style="background-color: white; box-sizing: border-box; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.88); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, "Noto Sans", sans-serif, "Apple Color Emoji", "Segoe UI Emoji", "Segoe UI Symbol", "Noto Color Emoji"; font-size: 14px;"><strong style="box-sizing